  "notes": [
    "Empty body hash is SHA-256 of the empty byte string, hex-encoded: e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855 — this is the canonical 'empty body' identifier.",
    "post_with_body case uses the SHA-256 of the ASCII string \"hello world\" (without a trailing newline) as the body hash.",
    "Nonces shown here are test-fixtures, not real entropy. Production nonces MUST carry at least 16 bytes of CSPRNG-derived randomness.",
